### Which @angular/* package(s) are relevant/related to the feature request?

core

### Description

I want a simple way to pass data into "router-outlet" child components


### Proposed solution

```ts
@Component({
    selector : 'main',
    template : `
        <router-outlet [data]="data"></router-outlet>
    `
})
export class MainComponent {
    data = 'test';
}
```

Retrive the data into the routed component

```ts
import {ROUTER_DATA} from '@angular/core';
import { Inject } from '@angular/core';

constructor(
   @Inject(ROUTER_DATA) public data: any
) { }
```

### Alternatives considered

Nothing

### Which @angular/* package(s) are relevant/related to the feature request?

core

### Description

Many times we want to perform some specific operation on different events, like delay, debounceTime, throttle with current implementation it is not possible to do it with in template.


### Proposed solution

We can introduce, event pipes, similar to pipes in angular but which can be applied to events.

some thing like,

```html
<input (input | debounceTime : 300)="onInputChange()"
```
```typescript
@EventPipe({
name: 'debounceTime'
})
extend class DebounceTimeEventPipe  {
  handle<T>(obs: Observable<T>, arg: number) : Observable<T> {
    return obs.pipe(debounceTime(arg));
  }
}
```

### Alternatives considered

I think this can also be performed by custom `EventManager`/`EventManagerPlugin` but current default implementation provide limited options and are not easily extendable and also lack documentation.

### What are you trying to do?

I'm having an issue with the mat-select where it isn't possible to define the item height externally.
When searching the issue I found #23838 which indicated to try the experimental version.
After following the instructions on [material-experimental/mdc-select](https://github.com/angular/components/tree/main/src/material-experimental/mdc-select) i receive a NG0300 error.
In my application I receive the following error: `NG0300: Multiple components match node with tagname mat-form-field: MatFormField and MatFormField.`
When creating the reproduction stackblitz and using the mat-select without a mat-form-field I receive the following error: NG0300: Multiple components match node with tagname mat-option: MatOption and MatOption.

I can't seem to figure out how to only import the experimental mat-select to check if this resolves my issue with the current "default" mat-select.

### What troubleshooting steps have you tried?

There's not much to troubleshoot, if I import anything from material-experimental my application no longer works.
I remove the import and "revert" to the default component my application works.

### Reproduction

Steps to reproduce:
